verbose_text: It was observed that, as in EA.hy926 cells, integrin alpha2 and beta3 significantly decreased at 5-10 min with inhibition of FAK, and were restored to a higher level at 10-30 min, consistently with the recovery of the pFAK level at 10-30 min; the beta1 subunit exhibited a stronger expression at 10-30 min; a gradually weakened expression level of the alpha5 subunit was associated with increasing duration of Y15 treatment, whereas the expression of alphaV exhibited a gradual decrease within 30 min and then remained stable (XREF_FIG).
